[ti:Water and the Traveller]
[00:00.54]Lesson 38|第38课
[00:02.41]Water and the traveller|水与旅行者
[00:09.59]What does this text describe?|这段文字描述了什么？
[00:13.50]Contamination of water supplies is usually due to poor sanitation close to water sources,|水源的污染通常是由于水源附近卫生条件差所导致的。
[00:21.30]sewage disposal into the sources themselves, leakage of sewage into distribution systems or contamination with industrial or farm waste.|污水被直接排放到水源中；污水泄漏到供水系统中；或者水源被工业或农业废弃物污染。
[00:32.17]Even if a piped water supply is safe at its source, it is not always safe by the time it reaches the tap.|即使管道输送的自来水在源头是安全的，但在到达水龙头时也不一定还是安全的。
[00:39.72]Intermittent tap-water supplies should be regarded as particularly suspect.|间歇性的自来水供应情况应该被视为非常可疑的（即可能存在问题或安全隐患）。
[00:45.76]Travellers on short trips to areas with water supplies of uncertain quality|前往水质不稳定的地区的短途旅行者
[00:51.08]should avoid drinking tap-water, or untreated water from any other source.|应避免饮用自来水或来自其他任何来源的未经处理的水。
[00:56.95]It is best to keep to hot drinks, bottled or canned drinks of well-known brand names-international standard of water treatment are usually followed at bottling plants.|最好选择热饮，或者选择知名品牌生产的瓶装或罐装饮料。这些饮料的生产工厂通常采用国际标准的水处理工艺。
[01:08.27]Carbonated drinks are acidic, and slightly safer.|碳酸饮料呈酸性，相对来说比较“安全”（即对健康的影响较小）。
[01:12.24]Make sure that all bottles are opened in your presence, and that their rims are clean and dry.|请确保所有瓶子都在你的监督下被打开，并且瓶口的边缘保持干净、干燥的状态。
[01:19.14]Boiling is always a good way of treating water.|煮沸始终是处理水的一种有效方法。
[01:22.36]Some hotels supply boiled water on request and this can be used for drinking, or for brushing teeth.|有些酒店会根据客人的要求提供煮沸的水，这种水可以用来饮用或刷牙。
[01:29.49]Portable boiling elements that can boil small quantities of water are useful when the right voltage of electricity is available.|便携式煮水装置在能够提供合适电压的电力条件下非常实用，因为它们可以用来烧开少量的水。
[01:37.86]Refuse politely any cold drink from an unknown source.|礼貌地拒绝任何来自陌生人的冷饮。
[01:43.22]Ice is only as safe as the water from which it is made,|冰的安全性取决于构成它的水的质量。
[01:46.79]and should not be put in drinks unless it is known to be safe.|除非确定它是安全的，否则不应该将其添加到饮料中。
[01:51.80]Drinks can be cooled by placing them on ice rather than adding ice to them.|饮料可以通过将其放在冰块上来冷却，而不是在饮料中加入冰块。
[01:58.17]Alcohol may be a medical disinfectant, but should not be relied upon to sterilize water.|酒精虽然可以用作医疗消毒剂，但不应依赖它来对水进行杀菌处理。
[02:05.57]Ethanol is more effective at a concentration of 50-70 percent;|乙醇在浓度为50%至70%时效果更佳。
[02:10.72]below 20 per cent, its bactericidal action is negligible.|当其浓度低于20%时，其杀菌效果几乎可以忽略不计。
[02:15.91]Spirits labelled 95 proof contain only about 47 per cent alcohol.|标有“95度”酒精含量的酒类，实际上只含有大约47%的酒精。
[02:22.63]Beware of methylated alcohol,|请注意：甲醇（methylated alcohol）是一种危险的物质，摄入后可能对人体造成严重伤害甚至致命。
[02:24.89]which is very poisonous and should never be added to drinking water.|这种物质具有很强的毒性，绝对不能被添加到饮用水中。
[02:30.71]If no other safe water supply can be obtained,|如果无法获得其他安全的水源，
[02:34.45]tap water that is too hot to touch can be left to cool and is generally safe to drink.|如果自来水太烫而无法直接饮用，可以将其放凉后再喝；通常情况下，这样的水是安全可饮用的。
[02:41.50]Those planning a trip to remote areas, or intending to live in countries where drinking water is not readily available,|那些计划前往偏远地区旅行，或者打算生活在饮用水不易获得的国家的人，
[02:49.29]should know about the various possible methods for making water safe.|应该了解各种使水变得安全的方法。
